
 Package		- class
 Reference	- class object
 Subrouting - method 

 Class is defined in the .pm file.

 To construct an object use new(). It will always pass a class name as the first element in @_.

 To create an instance of a class you create a reference that knows what class it belongs to. The built-in
 function bless is used to bless the reference to a class

 object = bless $reference, $classname;

 Get Perl version from within script:    print $^V;
